HEADWORD: Do-little
<hw>Do"-lit`tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who performs
little though professing much.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great talkers are commonly <qex>dolittles</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Richardson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dolium</ent>⟦br⟧
